---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout title="Security Architecture" description="AskSLM's security architecture ensures zero cloud exposure, hardware-bound encryption, full audit trails, and compliance with HIPAA, SOC 2, FISMA, and ISO 27001.">

  <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
  <section class="hero-gradient relative overflow-hidden pt-32 pb-20 md:pt-44 md:pb-32">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03]" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg class="h-full w-full" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern id="hex-security" width="56" height="100" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse" patternTransform="scale(2)">
            <path d="M28 66L0 50V18L28 2l28 16v32L28 66z" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" class="text-teal" />
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#hex-security)" />
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-navy-700 bg-navy-900/80 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs text-slate-400 mb-8">
          <span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-teal animate-pulse"></span>
          Security & Compliance
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-[1.08]">
          Security is not a feature
          <br />
          <span class="text-gradient">we added.</span>
        </h1>

        <p class="mt-4 text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-300 tracking-tight">
          It is the architecture.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-6 text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-400 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
          Every design decision in AskSLM -- from hardware-bound encryption to model provenance tracking -- exists because regulated industries demand it. Compliance is not a checkbox. It is the reason we exist.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-teal px-6 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-navy-950 transition-all duration-200 hover:bg-teal-dim hover:glow-teal">
            Schedule a Security Review
            <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="/platform" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-navy-700 px-6 py-3 text-base font-medium text-slate-300 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-slate-600 hover:text-ice">
            Platform Overview
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Security pillars strip -->
      <div class="mt-16 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        {['Zero Cloud Exposure', 'Hardware-Bound Encryption', 'Full Audit Trails', 'Role-Based Access', 'Model Provenance'].map(text => (
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-navy-700 bg-navy-900/50 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-slate-300">
            <svg class="h-3.5 w-3.5 text-teal" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 003 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285z" />
            </svg>
            {text}
          </span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SECTION 1: SECURITY ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW ===== -->
  <section class="section-border py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Security architecture overview</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
            AskSLM processes everything locally. Your data never crosses a network boundary you don't control. There is no cloud component, no external API dependency, and no mode in which sensitive data leaves your infrastructure.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-10 space-y-8">
            {[
              {
                title: 'Local-only data flow',
                desc: 'Every query, every response, and every training job runs within your infrastructure perimeter. There is no "hybrid cloud" fallback. The architecture is physically incapable of sending data externally during inference.',
              },
              {
                title: 'Hardware-bound encryption',
                desc: 'Trusted Execution Environments (TEEs) provide hardware-level encryption. Even if someone physically accesses a server, models and data remain cryptographically locked to the authorized hardware.',
              },
              {
                title: 'Network isolation by design',
                desc: 'The inference engine requires no outbound network connections during operation. Air-gapped deployment is fully supported for the most sensitive environments.',
              },
            ].map(item => (
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ice mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Data flow visualization -->
        <div class="card-surface rounded-2xl p-8 lg:mt-12">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ice mb-6">What stays local</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { label: 'Queries & responses', local: true },
              { label: 'Training data', local: true },
              { label: 'Model weights', local: true },
              { label: 'Audit logs', local: true },
              { label: 'User credentials', local: true },
              { label: 'Document embeddings', local: true },
              { label: 'RAG knowledge base', local: true },
              { label: 'API keys & tokens', local: true },
            ].map(row => (
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg border border-navy-800 bg-navy-950/50 px-4 py-3">
                <span class="text-sm text-slate-300">{row.label}</span>
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-teal">
                  <svg class="h-3.5 w-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  On-premise only
                </span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
          <div class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-navy-800 bg-navy-950/50 px-4 py-3 text-center">
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-400">Data sent to external cloud:</span>
            <span class="block text-2xl font-bold text-teal font-mono mt-1">0 bytes</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SECTION 2: DATA PROTECTION ===== -->
  <section class="section-border py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Data protection</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-400">
          Multilayered protections for your most sensitive information. Every byte accounted for. Every access controlled.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            title: 'Zero cloud usage',
            desc: 'No data is sent to third-party clouds during inference, training, or any other operation. This is not a setting you enable -- it is a structural impossibility.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M2.25 15a4.5 4.5 0 004.5 4.5H18a3.75 3.75 0 001.332-7.257 3 3 0 00-3.758-3.848 5.25 5.25 0 00-10.233 2.33A4.502 4.502 0 002.25 15z" />`,
          },
          {
            title: 'On-site processing',
            desc: 'All inference, training, and data retrieval occurs within your hardware or SLM appliance. Your data paths are fully auditable and physically contained.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M2.25 21h19.5m-18-18v18m10.5-18v18m6-13.5V21M6.75 6.75h.75m-.75 3h.75m-.75 3h.75m3-6h.75m-.75 3h.75m-.75 3h.75M6.75 21v-3.375c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125V21M3 3h12m-.75 4.5H21m-3.75 3H21" />`,
          },
          {
            title: 'Encryption at rest and in transit',
            desc: 'Data encrypted at rest with hardware-bound keys. All inter-component communication uses TLS. Trusted Execution Environments provide an additional hardware encryption layer.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M16.5 10.5V6.75a4.5 4.5 0 10-9 0v3.75m-.75 11.25h10.5a2.25 2.25 0 002.25-2.25v-6.75a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25-2.25H6.75a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25 2.25v6.75a2.25 2.25 0 002.25 2.25z" />`,
          },
          {
            title: 'Role-based access control',
            desc: 'Granular RBAC ensures only authorized users and systems interact with specific models and data. Define roles by department, clearance level, or use case.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M15 19.128a9.38 9.38 0 002.625.372 9.337 9.337 0 004.121-.952 4.125 4.125 0 00-7.533-2.493M15 19.128v-.003c0-1.113-.285-2.16-.786-3.07M15 19.128v.106A12.318 12.318 0 018.624 21c-2.331 0-4.512-.645-6.374-1.766l-.001-.109a6.375 6.375 0 0111.964-3.07M12 6.375a3.375 3.375 0 11-6.75 0 3.375 3.375 0 016.75 0zm8.25 2.25a2.625 2.625 0 11-5.25 0 2.625 2.625 0 015.25 0z" />`,
          },
          {
            title: 'Segregated storage',
            desc: 'Model weights and user data are stored in separate, isolated environments. Cross-environment leakage is architecturally prevented at the storage layer.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M20.25 6.375c0 2.278-3.694 4.125-8.25 4.125S3.75 8.653 3.75 6.375m16.5 0c0-2.278-3.694-4.125-8.25-4.125S3.75 4.097 3.75 6.375m16.5 0v11.25c0 2.278-3.694 4.125-8.25 4.125s-8.25-1.847-8.25-4.125V6.375m16.5 0v3.75m-16.5-3.75v3.75m16.5 0v3.75C20.25 16.153 16.556 18 12 18s-8.25-1.847-8.25-4.125v-3.75m16.5 0c0 2.278-3.694 4.125-8.25 4.125s-8.25-1.847-8.25-4.125" />`,
          },
          {
            title: 'Policy enforcement',
            desc: 'Automated policy enforcement blocks unauthorized data flows and access patterns. Policies are defined centrally and applied consistently across the platform.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M10.5 6h9.75M10.5 6a1.5 1.5 0 11-3 0m3 0a1.5 1.5 0 10-3 0M3.75 6H7.5m3 12h9.75m-9.75 0a1.5 1.5 0 01-3 0m3 0a1.5 1.5 0 00-3 0m-3.75 0H7.5m9-6h3.75m-3.75 0a1.5 1.5 0 01-3 0m3 0a1.5 1.5 0 00-3 0m-9.75 0h9.75" />`,
          },
        ].map(card => (
          <div class="card-surface rounded-xl p-6 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-navy-600">
            <div class="h-10 w-10 rounded-lg bg-teal/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-teal" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <Fragment set:html={card.icon} />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ice mb-2">{card.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">{card.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SECTION 3: COMPLIANCE FRAMEWORKS ===== -->
  <section class="section-border py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Compliance frameworks</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-400">
          Built from the ground up for the frameworks that govern your industry.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            framework: 'HIPAA',
            status: 'Architecture aligned',
            statusColor: 'teal',
            industry: 'Healthcare',
            details: [
              'PHI never leaves your infrastructure',
              'Full audit trails for every AI interaction',
              'BAA-ready architecture',
              'Segregated data storage prevents cross-contamination',
            ],
          },
          {
            framework: 'SOC 2',
            status: 'In progress',
            statusColor: 'teal',
            industry: 'Enterprise',
            details: [
              'Trust service criteria alignment',
              'Continuous monitoring and logging',
              'Access controls and authentication',
              'Incident response procedures',
            ],
          },
          {
            framework: 'FISMA',
            status: 'Architecture aligned',
            statusColor: 'teal',
            industry: 'Government',
            details: [
              'Air-gapped deployment supported',
              'NIST 800-53 control mapping',
              'Continuous monitoring capabilities',
              'Authority to Operate documentation support',
            ],
          },
          {
            framework: 'ISO 27001',
            status: 'Roadmap',
            statusColor: 'slate-400',
            industry: 'International',
            details: [
              'Information security management system alignment',
              'Risk assessment and treatment processes',
              'Asset management and access control',
              'Operational security procedures',
            ],
          },
        ].map(card => (
          <div class="card-surface rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col transition-all duration-300 hover:border-navy-600">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
              <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-ice font-mono">{card.framework}</span>
              <span class={`inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[10px] font-mono font-bold tracking-widest uppercase px-2.5 py-1 rounded ${card.statusColor === 'teal' ? 'text-teal bg-teal/10' : 'text-slate-400 bg-slate-400/10'}`}>
                <span class={`h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full ${card.statusColor === 'teal' ? 'bg-teal' : 'bg-slate-400'}`}></span>
                {card.status}
              </span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-4">{card.industry}</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 flex-1">
              {card.details.map(detail => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-slate-400">
                  <svg class="h-4 w-4 text-teal flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  <span class="leading-relaxed">{detail}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 card-surface rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
          Compliance status is presented honestly. "Architecture aligned" means the technical architecture supports the framework's requirements. Formal certification timelines available upon request.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SECTION 4: MODEL INTEGRITY ===== -->
  <section class="section-border py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Model integrity & provenance</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
            Every model running on your infrastructure is verified, versioned, and traceable. You know exactly what trained it, who built it, and when it changed.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-10 space-y-8">
            {[
              {
                title: 'Cryptographic signing',
                desc: 'Every model build is cryptographically signed. The inference engine verifies signatures before execution, ensuring only authorized, unmodified models run on your hardware.',
              },
              {
                title: 'Version tracking and lineage',
                desc: 'Complete version history for every model. Track every update, every dataset change, and every configuration modification with full lineage documentation.',
              },
              {
                title: 'Training data provenance',
                desc: 'Transparent documentation of training sources for every model. Know exactly what data informed the model\'s behavior -- critical for regulatory audits and liability management.',
              },
              {
                title: 'Integrity checks before execution',
                desc: 'Models undergo integrity verification before they process any data. Tampered or unverified models are rejected automatically at the engine level.',
              },
            ].map(item => (
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ice mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Model provenance visual -->
        <div class="card-surface rounded-2xl p-8 lg:mt-12">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ice mb-6">Model lifecycle security</h3>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            {[
              { step: '01', label: 'Build', desc: 'Model trained on verified, documented data sources by authorized vendor' },
              { step: '02', label: 'Sign', desc: 'Cryptographic signature applied to model build artifact' },
              { step: '03', label: 'Verify', desc: 'Integrity check validates signature and provenance before deployment' },
              { step: '04', label: 'Deploy', desc: 'Model deployed to your engine via encrypted pipeline' },
              { step: '05', label: 'Monitor', desc: 'Continuous version tracking, access logging, and anomaly detection' },
              { step: '06', label: 'Audit', desc: 'Full trail available for compliance review at any time' },
            ].map(item => (
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="text-sm font-mono font-bold text-teal mt-0.5">{item.step}</span>
                <div class="flex-1 pb-6 border-b border-navy-800 last:border-0 last:pb-0">
                  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-ice">{item.label}</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">{item.desc}</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SECTION 5: AUDIT & GOVERNANCE ===== -->
  <section class="section-border py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Audit & governance</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-400">
          Complete visibility into every AI interaction. The audit trail your compliance team requires.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            title: 'Audit trails',
            desc: 'Every model interaction logged with timestamp, user, query hash, model version, and response metadata. Exportable for external compliance review.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M19.5 14.25v-2.625a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375h-1.5A1.125 1.125 0 0113.5 7.125v-1.5a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375H8.25m0 12.75h7.5m-7.5 3H12M10.5 2.25H5.625c-.621 0-1.125.504-1.125 1.125v17.25c0 .621.504 1.125 1.125 1.125h12.75c.621 0 1.125-.504 1.125-1.125V11.25a9 9 0 00-9-9z" />`,
          },
          {
            title: 'Logging & monitoring',
            desc: 'Real-time monitoring of system health, model performance, and access patterns. Alerts on anomalous behavior or policy violations.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M3 13.125C3 12.504 3.504 12 4.125 12h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v6.75C7.5 20.496 6.996 21 6.375 21h-2.25A1.125 1.125 0 013 19.875v-6.75zM9.75 8.625c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v11.25c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V8.625zM16.5 4.125c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25C20.496 3 21 3.504 21 4.125v15.75c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V4.125z" />`,
          },
          {
            title: 'Policy enforcement',
            desc: 'Define and enforce data handling policies centrally. Automated checks ensure workloads align with internal and regulatory requirements.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 003 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285z" />`,
          },
          {
            title: 'Incident readiness',
            desc: 'Documented incident response procedures. Threat detection and anomaly monitoring. Vulnerability scanning and environment hardening.',
            icon: `<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126zM12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z" />`,
          },
        ].map(card => (
          <div class="card-surface rounded-xl p-6 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-navy-600">
            <div class="h-10 w-10 rounded-lg bg-teal/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-teal" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <Fragment set:html={card.icon} />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-ice mb-2">{card.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">{card.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== CTA ===== -->
  <section class="relative py-20 md:py-28 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-navy-950 via-navy-900 to-navy-950"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.04]" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg class="h-full w-full" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern id="hex-security-cta" width="56" height="100" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse" patternTransform="scale(1.5)">
            <path d="M28 66L0 50V18L28 2l28 16v32L28 66z" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" class="text-teal" />
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#hex-security-cta)" />
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Have security questions?</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gradient">Talk to our team.</p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-400 max-w-xl mx-auto">
